# Phase 1 only — Kconfig-supplied bearer token for the /mcp/* HTTP endpoints
# (Claude Code Channel adapter target). Phase 2+ will move this to NVS so it's
# configurable from the BLE / Wi-Fi settings pages without a re-flash; this
# Kconfig knob then goes away.
menu "Stack-chan Channel API (Claude Code)"

    config MCP_API_TOKEN
        string "Bearer token for /mcp/* endpoints (Phase 1)"
        default ""
        help
            Static bearer token that the Channel adapter sends in the
            `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header of every /mcp/* request.
            Empty string disables the endpoints entirely (they return 404 so
            Cloudflare Tunnel can be left wired without exposing a live API).
            Put the real value in sdkconfig.defaults.local, NOT in the
            committed sdkconfig.defaults — the token is the only thing
            protecting the API from anyone who reaches the tunnel.

endmenu
